parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can lead to the seat belt becoming unlatched while driving, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle fails to latch properly
the seat belt comes out of the buckle
the buckle breaks
the seat belt releases itself while driving
the seat belt will not release
the red release button is solid hard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to catch fire, resulting in potential harm to occupants and damage to the vehicle. In some cases, the ignition switch may not ignite if the gear shift is not completely up, leading to difficulty starting the vehicle.
symptoms: The ignition switch does not ignite
the vehicle catches fire
the ignition switch shorts out
the ignition switch fails to function properly
the vehicle is difficult to start.

symptoms: The seat belt buckle fails
the seat belt does not latch

the seat belt is inoperable.
